descriptions.name: Full name
descriptions.given-name: Given name (in some Western cultures, also known as the first name)
descriptions.additional-name: Additional names (in some Western cultures, also known as middle names, forenames other than the first name)
descriptions.family-name: Family name (in some Western cultures, also known as the last name or surname)
descriptions.nickname: Nickname, screen name, handle: a typically short name used instead of the full name
descriptions.organization-title: Job title (e.g., 'Software Engineer', 'Senior Vice President', 'Deputy Managing Director')
descriptions.new-password: A new password (e.g., when creating an account or changing a password)
descriptions.current-password: The current password for the account identified by the username field (e.g., when logging in)
descriptions.organization: Company name corresponding to the person, address, or contact information in the other fields associated with this field
descriptions.address-line1: Street address (one line per field, line 1)
descriptions.address-line2: Street address (one line per field, line 2)
descriptions.address-line3: Street address (one line per field, line 3)
descriptions.address-level4: The most fine-grained administrative level, in addresses with four administrative levels
descriptions.address-level3: The third administrative level, in addresses with three or more administrative levels
descriptions.address-level2: The second administrative level, in addresses with two or more administrative levels; in the countries with two administrative levels, this would typically be the city, town, village, or other locality within which the relevant street address is found
descriptions.address-level1: The broadest administrative level in the address, i.e., the province within which the locality is found; for example, in the US, this would be the state; in Switzerland it would be the canton; in the UK, the post town
descriptions.postal-code: Postal code, post code, ZIP code, CEDEX code (if CEDEX, append 'CEDEX', and the dissement, if relevant, to the address-level2 field)
descriptions.cc-name: Full name as given on the payment instrument
descriptions.cc-given-name: Given name as given on the payment instrument (in some Western cultures, also known as the first name)
descriptions.cc-additional-name: Additional names given on the payment instrument (in some Western cultures, also known as middle names, forenames other than the first name)
descriptions.cc-family-name: Family name given on the payment instrument (in some Western cultures, also known as the last name or surname)
descriptions.cc-number: Code identifying the payment instrument (e.g., the credit card number)
descriptions.cc-exp: Expiration date of the payment instrument
descriptions.cc-exp-month: Month component of the expiration date of the payment instrument
descriptions.cc-exp-year: Year component of the expiration date of the payment instrument
descriptions.cc-csc: Security code for the payment instrument (also known as the card security code (CSC), card validation code (CVC), card verification value (CVV), signature panel code (SPC), credit card ID (CCID), etc)
descriptions.transaction-currency: The currency that the user would prefer the transaction to use
descriptions.transaction-amount: The amount that the user would like for the transaction (e.g., when entering a bid or sale price)
descriptions.url: Home page or other Web page corresponding to the company, person, address, or contact information in the other fields associated with this field
descriptions.photo: Photograph, icon, or other image corresponding to the company, person, address, or contact information in the other fields associated with this field
descriptions.tel: Full telephone number, including country code
descriptions.tel-country-code: Country code component of the telephone number
descriptions.tel-national: Telephone number without the county code component, with a country-internal prefix applied if applicable
descriptions.tel-area-code: Area code component of the telephone number, with a country-internal prefix applied if applicable
descriptions.tel-local: Telephone number without the country code and area code components
descriptions.tel-local-prefix: First part of the component of the telephone number that follows the area code, when that component is split into two components
descriptions.tel-local-suffix: Second part of the component of the telephone number that follows the area code, when that component is split into two components
descriptions.impp: URL representing an instant messaging protocol endpoint (for example, 'aim:goim?screenname=example' or 'xmpp:fred@example.net')
